  "prompt": "Who are the Impractical Jokers?",
  "response": "The Impractical Jokers are a comedy troupe known for their hidden camera reality comedy series that first premiered on TruTV in December 2011. The group consists of four friends from Staten Island, New York: Joe Gatto, Sal Vulcano, Brian Quinn (known as Q), and James Murray (often referred to as Murr). \n\nIn the show, the guys challenge each other to perform embarrassing and outrageous tasks in public while being filmed by hidden cameras. The humor often comes from their improvisation and how the public reacts to their antics. They also partake in various comedy challenges and games throughout the series, with the loser facing humorous consequences.\n\nOver the years, the show has gained a significant following, leading to live tours, spin-offs, and even a feature film. The group is known for their camaraderie and the dynamic between the members, which enhances their comedic interactions.",
